\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember approximately what the hours were for that half-crown a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well she'd leave home about eight in the morning and get back about six at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And she'd be walking part of that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Walking part of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 So she'd do approximately how many hours work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I should say she'd do - er - easy eight hours a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 With your mother working - who looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well me grandmother looked after us as well as she could but we used to - er - we had quite a lot of shops in those days 
- that had cooked dinners. One could get a bowl of pea soup for a penny. We had pea soup for our dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Up 'til when you left school, I'd like to hear about life at home when you were a child. How many rooms were there in the house in Chadwick Street, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
There was only four rooms - there was a kitchen, a parlour, a scullery and two upstairs and we - er - often or not had a lodger in the parlour and we shared the other - and they had their bed in there as well and we shared the - we
 shared the other - er - parts of the house between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 So you did have a lodger in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your mother have any help in the house - did she have anyone paid to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. She did all the - in those days w
e used to watch the kitchen - wash the kitchen - and it were flagged floors. And we used brown-stone them then put sand on so that when you ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Sanded them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Sand - sand all round. You could get sand from sandbone yard opposite Chadwick Street w
hich was occupied by a man named Bill Ridgeway and - er - he - we used to go for the sand and when they used to wash it clean - and I used to do the cleaning of the floors - well me grandmother used to tell me to do the corners and the middle'd do itself 
-
 see that - er - when you'd washed it and stoned it - brown-stone it - used to put this sand on because it was easier - the dirt was easier to get up and of course. Oh yes, we put the sand on the top when it was - er - and of course it was easy to sweep u
p when - er - when you was ready for cleaning it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 It was done at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your father or mother mend or make the family's clothes - or did they repair shoes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - we - we - I 
- er - I remember that we - we all wore clogs in those days. And went - to many of them as didn't have clogs or shoes went to school in their bare feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 In winter too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 In winter too. There was no such a thing as feeding us - er - I used to - er 
- on a Saturday to a man named Brown - Bill Brown - as had a shop opposite - er - Taggett Street and I'd go with him to the market - we'd be there at six o'clock - we'd buy all that we wanted and we'd come back and set it out on the stall and I'd mind it 
- this was stall - 'til eleven o'clock at night. I'd be only about ten years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 This was while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Mmm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were the clothes always new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh we only had - and that was Whit Monday - Whit Sunday - then on Whit Monday it'
d be in Bobby Thomsons which was the pawnshop round the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Can you remember where your clothes were bought? And when they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well they would be bought just before Whitsun time because everybody - er - as you know, used to all - er
 - have their best on a Whit Sunday and I think that my first suit was made at Littlewoods - in Regent Road - remember it at all - opposite Regent Road baths - he was a church warden at St. Bartholomews church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No I don't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about shoes, Mr Lester, would your mother or father ever mend them?
