Me father used to put leather between the irons - irons of our clogs - they were irons you see round there and on the heel - he put leather in the centre - leather in the centre 
- er - er - over the wood. So you see - that would prevent you having - ironed too often you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You would think the iron would still protrude beyond the leather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No, as a matter of fact, I wore clogs for many years and I felt no - muc
h warmer to me feet than shoes. And - er - now what about me - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Can you tell me if the shoes were always new or were they ever secondhand - passed down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We had new shoes 'cos you could get a pair then for two and eleven, quite easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your father ever help your mother with any jobs in the house - cleaning or cooking or washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - immediately he'd had his tea he used to go out and have a pint of bitter and stay there 'til it was throwing out time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about fires - did he ever light them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
We - er - we - er - we burnt coal and - er - used to buy coke and - coke was two buckets a penny in those days and we used to have two men come round with - er - er - a donkey and cart and they'd be shouting 'Coke' and we used to go
 out and get two buckets for a penny, which - which augmented the coal allowance that we got - we could get a quarter of coal in those days for tuppence ha'penny and I used to go and get the quarter of coal and carry it - at a man named Lonsdale who'll ha
ve kept a shop at the top - er - er - kept - kept a yard at the top of Chadwick Street in .....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your father light the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 He, no - no, no, me mum - one of the children, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he do any decorating or improvements to the house, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes - well - well we do a little bit of paper hanging between us but it - the kitchen - in order to - er - throw light into the kitchen - we were - it - er - it were showing a blank wall, you see, and the back yard wall there and white washe
d this twice a year so as to make it light in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he ever help to dress you or undress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, he never took us out at all, I don't think, did old chappie - just one for his booze - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well, we looked after ourselves because I think all the neighbours - with children of the neighbours - o
f the neighbours - it was all like that, because they all got to go out leaving a bit - and they all had someone living in the - in the front room and I remember the time when we burnt oil lamps instead of gas or electricity 'cos there was none. So we had
 a paraffin lamp on the kitchen table and we lit it every night and turned it out when we was going to bed.
