\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I went for most of the errands, you know, as - 'cos I was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid686647\charrsid7297954 eldest}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 you see, and - er - and we used to go - I used to get our bread from a place called Lukes's on Regent Road - opposite - opposite where Groves - er - by the Global terrace - do you know down there at all. Opposite that were Lukes and we used 
a loaf - buy a loaf for tuppence with make-weight - what we called make-weight. If there was a piece of cake knocking about that - that couldn't get rid of - they put this on the top - we had to make - make - wait before we go home.
