Y - No, we stood - we used to stand at the door. But in the old days when anybody died we used to visit them in the parlour and the - - the curate outside taking the two and three to see th
e corpse. And of course - I remember - these funerals we used to think - er - we'll have to see this funeral and - er - they - sometimes they - they'd leave it in their will or leave it verbally that they had to have four horses instead of two and they al
w
ays had to be black - black ones. It remember two undertakers in Ordsall Lane - was a man that there now - Tetlow - he died but his daughter-in-law's carried on - and another man named Chee - down the lane - Chee had the most trade 'cos they said he could
 - he put em away best.
