-
 they used to go out on every bank holiday and never went anywhere - at any other time - with the pony and trap and hundreds turned out to see them go - but - because they wanted to look at Mrs. Brown's new hat. And - and that was the only time they would
 
- went out where they had - there was three of them - there was him and her and they had one girl - Dahlia - she's passed on since and everybody used to turn out at the corner to see Brown going out with his pony and cart and - I'd washed and polished - a
nd - er - she had her hat on and everybody used to pass remark.
