Oh yes we did that because - er - and then I - 'course I remember all the funerals as took place in the street and - er - and quite a lot of the old neighbours has pass
ed on - but it was very funny that they always laid them out in the parlour, you know, and they all used to go to have - to interview 'em for the last time and it was Friday night 'cos they always made a point of burying Saturday 'cos you see they wasn't 
on five days in those days - they left off at twelve o'clock at Saturday dinner time and we had funerals in the afternoon - Weest or Hedgecroft you see - we haven't got them now you know.
