\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - no, no ruling or - from the sanitary or the health inspectors - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did you spend your Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well we - we spent our Sundays more or less going to the places of worship. We - er - I - I went to St Bartholomews Sunday morning, then perhaps Longford Street Mission in the afternoon. There was a man named Johnny Richar
dson who was running it at that time - he had a shop in Ordsall Lane - er - a secondhand clothing - secondhand furniture shop - and he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  then there was Alfred Allsop who started it, you know, - started this - er -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was it Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - it was - er - a Mission - just a mission, I think it's still there - and the - and had a holiday camp but I'm not quite sure whether that's still going or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, we had the same - and then we put a - put an extra polish on our clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you play games or did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, we played on Sunday in one of the neighbours 'cos we used to have a - when they lived in the parlour we
 used to have a pin and a button and put it in the - stick it in and out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Put it in the window?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We did - and we were clapping all the time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did they think it was wrong to work on Sunday - your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I can never remember any Sunday work at all in those days - there was only sufficient work of a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about in the house though - did your mother work in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh she always cleaned the place, of course it was - that was natural you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. They never went anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you go to Sunday school. Wood Street Mission would be your Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 In the afternoon - Longford Hall at night - it would all depend on what we got from these pla
ces for special treats - see there was crowds of children went - we - we - I think we'd have to pay about a penny for a ticket to take us up from Hulme Locks - you Hulme Locks - no from Dawson Street - you know where Regent Bridge is - well it's the conti
nue right across there into Manchester - starts the Mancurian Way - on the right is a canal - that was Hulme Locks - we used to go there and - er - go to Lymne and or this town.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Lymne in Cheshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I think it - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 where\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  the canal round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 It must be opposite the fields across there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 That's it - the Bridgewater - the Bridgewater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And you used to come up to here did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Used to come up here for a picnic and - er - we used to - er - it was always a bit of fun because somebody 
sure to - always somebody sure to fall in, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 That was the fun fishing them out was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What other sort of activities did you have at church or at chapel - social things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well they were mostly singing you know, and the - 
er - there were - er - strictly religious in those days - with the people that took these jobs on and we'd sing all the old hymns and we'd sing - er - I think of them now once or twice when I make out to my place and we sing - er - Dare to be a Daniel and
 Dare to Stand Alone, you know it - yes. Dare to have a Purpose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you in a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. Wasn't in the choir but I used to - er - enjoy the singing though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did it run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes most of them were temperance people, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No, but they used - er - to - er - I remember quite well when we had the - er - the - er - processions on a Sunday perhaps - that were - they'd have a lorry - perhaps two lorries - one with the - er - the home that didn't take
 drink and the other with the home that did. Yes - two scenes, you know, and this were it one that took drink was in rags and - and them that didn't take it was dressed in their best, you see, the publicans didn't like it you know, but - but we used to en
joy it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 This was run by the chapel was it? I've never heard of that before. And this used to go around the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes, oh yes. It'd go round the town. With - er - with a band and quite a lot of workers perhaps - and what walking behind, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And what was the idea of it - was it to get people to sign the pledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 That's it. Exactly. They - no I never signed the pledge 'cos I never took it much, you see, just an odd drink like I might tonight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have this procedure though at chapel - signing the pledge - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Oh yes. Oh yes. I remember us - at Longford Hall getting the drunkards in - when they'd had what they call a drunkards raid of Saturday night and they ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Drunkards raid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes. They
'd wait for all the pubs - all the fellers coming out of the pubs and they'd link them up you know and take them to Longford - for midnight service and get them to sign the pledge and go for them next day to come to the Mission you know. But some of them 
made good but others just couldn't do - do without the drink you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 It did work for some of them though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh it did that - it did. I was only talking to a lad last week - named Jimmy Renny - I was telling him this about his father - they had hi
s father about half a dozen times in Longford Hall - he couldn't really hold out like - without having a glass - and they had him signing the pledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he belong to any other club organized by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - er - we never bothered about grace - but - er - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 we had}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - we used to say it before we left - er - school - when we got back you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Never. We've had 'em since we've been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617120 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  and had the children was at home which is a different life altogether you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No he didn't - he were true blue and you couldn't shake him from it see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he talk about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - er - no I don't think he did because we didn't know what it was all about and I don't think they did either, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You don't know why he held the views then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well his father was true blue - and 
like you get them today - what they're mothers and fathers was their the same you see and - we get it today that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 They were all true blue really - yes - they voted for Groves - and - er - Jimmy Groves was the M.P. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5660644\charrsid7297954 before Hilaire Belloc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - you know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5660644\charrsid7297954 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5660644\charrsid7297954 Hilaire Belloc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 was the better man of the two - he was a Liberal you know - there was no Labour candidate in those days, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And who got in at that election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 They both got in - one time - one one time o
ne the next. Jimmy Groves got in one time and - and the people that had to vote in those days was only man and wife there was no such a thing as lodgers votes and that kind of thing - only two votes a house - that was the man and wife who were the occupie
rs you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And you know which party they voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their 
jobs or the house if they voted differently from their employers - do you know if your father ever felt this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
I - no - but I felt it 'cos I - I - I - you - the old Esso Petroleum Company was the - er - I was the - er - on threepence an hour a day - a
nd we daren't read the Daily Herald - we had to go in the corner to read it and we daren't know they were coming say to you - mark you their different today - and they been different for a long time - but - they - they were real slave drivers in those day
s and we had to get in a corner to read the labour papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What year was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 That'd be 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 But do you think your father ever felt this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I don't think they ever discussed politics in the workshops in those days but they do today as
 you know - you see - and that's how they spread the gospel of the Labour party 'cos they've talked amongst one and other and then the Trade Unions have played a great part you see in - er - in - er - in the branch meetings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was your father ever a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he ever work for them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Never. Just went and voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well now - what do you mean by not doing their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 When they'd finished work - in their leisure time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Oh mother used to sit there mending our stockings and - er - because she used to knit them for us - oh yes - we had knitted stockings - as a matter of fact our boys used to wear them and wou
ldn't wear anything else when they were going to school - and we bought the Christmas presents instead of buying them toys - we - er - mother - er - Mrs Lester - making them pullovers and stockings they knitted with the tops - with a top like this - she u
sed to run a piece of red - red wool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And your mother used to do this too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - she used to do it too - she knitted - she mended our stockings and knitted them for us - she was a grand knitter was me mother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I don't think she did - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - perhaps she went and had a gill with me father but - er - that was - she couldn't afford a lot but she - she came home after she'd had about one or two but he used to stay until he couldn't drink no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 When father got home from work in the evening how many evenings a week do you think he spent at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I don't think he spent any - not even Sunday - I think he was always in the pub - he - h
e - er - he was on about - 'course Bennett beer in those days was only a penny a pint you know - see and of course if he was on twenty-seven shillings a week - and he gave me mother a pound, I think - he had seven bob which was a lot of money you know - b
u
t as you see things were so cheap - you could buy a dozen eggs for a bob you know and - er - and that kind of thing you see - and I've already said we could go to a - the greengrocers shop across - and what you are paying one and fourpence for two bananas
 now - we get whole pile - it were - was just a little bit soft for a penny you know and - er - 'cos they'd only have to throw them in the ash bin if we didn't and - er - they were all right you know. As lads we knew - anyway -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was your father ever in any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your mother go to the pub with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Not - er - no - she was - er - she - er - just had an odd glass but - er - I wouldn't say she was a drunkard, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your father take part in any sport or did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - and he never bet. He never - no - never had a bet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did they belong to any kind of savings club - in those days they had boot clubs and sick clubs and funeral clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, never. Oh they belonged to the - er - the - er - the
 society of funeral and that kind of thing then - 'course it wasn't as expensive them days as it was now, you see, and - er - of course - it was very funny as a boy - I told you, that they say I want four horses instead of two for the hearse you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
We got on very well together - it was rather strange that me brother was - when I took ill - my mother happened - this were in 19 - what are we in now - 1967 - on the eighteenth of December I had to
 have sleeping tablets, you know, 'cos I had so much thinking and thinking I can't sleep and I took three that night - I couldn't get to sleep and I kept taking them - and I rolled out of bed and I couldn't get up - I was unconscious - and my wife saw the
re were something wrong so she called the police and the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Your brother was a knocker-up in the city?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - he was a knocker - he was knocker-up all round - er - where we were born - Chadwick Street and Hudson Lane and he lived at 2A Warden
 Street and he used to knock them all up and he left to knock }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 here at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 three o'clock and it was three thirty when he had to knock next door - he daren't knock 'em half an hour before time - he'd have to come back to do the knocking. It was very funny - he g
ot to his last knock which was next door to where he lived and he - used - knocked on the window she thought oh he's forgot his keys and she went down and she just managed to get him in his chair then he'd gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was there anyone in the family you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - I was very fond of me grandmother - well she was seventy-two when she died - and she died in 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Why did you feel particularly close to your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well - she was rather kind - if she had a bit - a bit
 of anything - oh well - like a little bit of cake or anything like that - she would pass it on to us. But I always used to remember like having a - a pinch of snuff of her, you know - she used to take snuff. Yes - and I always used to like a pinch and sh
e used to put it on the back of me hand like that you know, from a little box she carried - and I used - it cleared me head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Which social class would you say you belonged to? In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Tell me what you just mean, love.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you working class - middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - we were ranked among the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What sort of people belonged to the same classed group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 They were all - you mean in those days? They were all in the same category. They all liked to go for a g
ill but they were all good to one another and - er - if you were - if anybody was sick - they used to come in and help a little bit to do the housework - and if there was anything they were cooking special they would bring it in. And I remember the family
 
doctor - er - that I used to go to for a bottle of medicine for me grandmother 'cos she had - er - a bit of bronchitis and that were doctor Cranner of Regent Road. Doctor - he had his surgery now, and they used to say oh it's Susannah is it, here y'are - 
a
nd he used to give me chlorodine and water and - er - they mixed it - they mixed it themselves in those days you know - and I can remember when there was no health insurance - they used to - here put it on the book - and they had the collector coming roun
d at weekend for sixpence to - er - we - to reduce - you know, to pay the doctor's bill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Can you remember being brought up to treat one sort of people differently from another? Were you told to touch your cap to someone - show respect to some? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh yes - we were always made to cap - take off our caps as we went into the - the home - you daren't go into the home with a cap on - no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were there people outside you were told to take off your caps to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No they never - we never bothered with - we - they were all neighbours and - er - we just - we never bothered }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 about anything}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  like that - I don't think they expected it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Can you tell me anything about other people who belonged to other classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 There was none in our district. Only - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was there anyone you called Sir or Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Only - only the headmasters and the teachers at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I never remember them havi
ng any disrespect because they were rather more, - er - a little - more or less liked because - er - they were just like themselves. There was never any trouble amongst them - they were very together. Some in the parlour as I've already told you - and per
haps - an odd case they'd have somebody in one of the bedrooms and - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were they ever called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh never. Never. No as a matter of fact we used to - er - if we wanted anything from them - we used to take a rise out of them - we'd go
 sit opposite the door and sing - I remember one woman was called Little Kate like and we used to sing something about poor old Kate, you know, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember, in the district, if anyone did anything wrong, that the neighbours didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes, I can remember - I can remember that in the next - oh yes - in the next street to us I can remember - 'cos I can picture it now - that - er - there was a chap there been knocking his wife about - we used to have the clothes lines in the street 
in those days with the prop - propped 'em up - and they didn't like this so when he come out they all had their props and they all battered him with the props. That were - I just can't think of his name now but - er - I remember that very - well that was 
i
n Prescott Street the next street - in the next street to us. And of course there was - there was always a fight at Saturday night at the pubs, you know, outside, and we used to look forward to a fight and the coppers coming down and picking them up takin
g
 them up to Regent Road and there was no police vans in them - Panda Cars then you know - they had to drag them through the streets. Then we used to turn out at Sunday morning to see the prison come to take them to Bedford Square you know, and they were h
orse drawn in them days you know - oh yes. Now what else do you want.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember any women who did anything wrong and the neighbours showed their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You don't remember them making dummies - imitations of anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - but if a woman was being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617120 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  and a man - they cut all his suiting - at the funeral - oh yes I remember that - I remember that in one case where - at Weest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 cemetery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  where they followed the all to the Weest cemetery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You mean when his wife died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
When his wife died they - they - they - and he come out to go into the coach the women would be each side of the door booing him and 'cos they knew the life that she led under him you see and that - er - oh I remember that very well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people? And did you come in contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well I think they had the greatest respect for a man named Patterson who was the Rector at St Bartholomews church, you know. I think he was
 the - er - the one and the one that they was afraid of was Sergeant Lewis - he was the court officer - and he used to deliver the summonses and anyone that went - that - er he wanted - he used to turn out at night - at twelve o'clock - and they wouldn't 
take the warrant - there was a warrant out for perhaps - er - oh arrears on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - er - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 laugh or something at the court and - and you'd have to pay to - neighbours had a child who was sixteen - he used to live - now every dinner time he
 came down Chadwick Street for his dinner 'cos he lived on what we call the Long Row - which is down now - which was a row of houses on Ordsall Lane. And - er - when they see him coming down the street with his stick, you know, and - coming to his lunch b
ecause he was in the court - for collecting and getting the summonses and warrants for the night, you know, he - they had a great deal of fear for Lewis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Who else was considered important, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - there was him - and he was a great 
visitor was Mr Patterson's - his rect - his - his curate was a man named - called Tom Shinwell - he finished up his career at - er - old \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 and he died - we - he used to be a great age when - and he was the - er - he was the er the rector there for many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes - we had - er - the - they didn't associate with anybody - we had a case there of - er - cook shops - Richardsons cake shop which was next to Browns - we could get a custard 
for a penny, you know, and - er - we used to - er - then if they had them Monday they couldn't sell them the next - used to call us in and give 'em us, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 The shopkeepers? Well, I always feel they felt they was a cl
ass amongst - among - er - belonging to themselves. And they're just closing a shop now because of the demolition - Howletts - he had - er - a shop up there when I was a boy and his mother and father would have passed on and Gilbert and Archie were two la
nds they - er - kept shop on going until - er - six months ago and that would be seventy years to my knowledge you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about the clergy - who do you think they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well they were better clergy in those days than they was today. You 
have to send for them if anybody's dying how - but they - they came - we hadn't to send for 'em in those days, you know, and they - they - thought it was - they felt it was part of their duty - they were more - shall I say they felt they were more called 
t
han they are today - got quite a lot go in for a living, you know - but not so with the - er - old parsons, I think that. And then, we had one who was a - er - belonged to the Roman Catholic Church - Father Sheen he'd only got to show these fellows the st
i
cks that hadn't - wouldn't go to work and had had a drink and by gum they were off. Yes, they had a great influence over them in those days though - don't think the priests got the same influence over them today as they had then, because as you know they 
just don't take no notice - well in those days, they saw Father Sheen coming down with the stick -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Who do you think they mixed with in their leisure time though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 I don't think they came out much, because they were only on poor salaries and er - 
and - and - I think - none as - I went to a church of England school we used to have to march from Dankig Street to St Bartholomews school on special days like - er - oh - er - Monday Thursday - oh yes - they - er - we - er - we had - it was a church scho
ol because - er - it was the nearest, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Ande - er - there's a man retired quite recent - well no it's not recently - be three - three or four years ago - I remember him becoming a teacher - and he retired from - as the headmaster from - er - St. - er
 - Andrews - you probably don't remember him - I've - I've reasons to believe he's living yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you know who the teachers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No they - they - they - er - they mixed amongst themselves in a small class - room that they had there and th
e headmaster and all had their sandwiches that they bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about farmers - did you know any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about employers - who did employers mix with in those days when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 They didn't mix with anybody - they - 
they - er - they er - kept to themselves, you know, because when they'd paid us our wages - and the men had their wages they knew that was the end of their liability.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What sort of people would you say went to church and what type went to chapel - did you notice any distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 
No - I think they were more or less the - er - the same - er - perhaps they - were dressed a little more than others but at St Bartholomews church they had some very, very good givers there, such as Littlewoods the - er - 
the - er - the tailors - and then there was Hamletts - Mr Hamlett who was the superintendent of the Sundays School and if you wanted a job at the san - cleaning department well you see - you must belong to Hamletts Bible Class - you didn't get one.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you think there was a different type of people went to church and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - I think - I think just the fancy of - how - which service they liked best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You didn't think there was any different social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about Roman Catholics - did you ever notice any prejudice towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No. No - they didn't bother about it - they all went to mass - and - er - they were more loyal to their religion than the Protestants 'cos whether it was the fear or - or - er - or because the
y had to go I can't say but they never missed, you know. And if they missed - er - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 Father would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 be round next day - Father Sheen - wanting to know why they weren't there, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Where you lived - did all the people in the working class have the sa
me standard of living or would you say there were different standards - different types of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - I should say they were more or less all the same with the exception of one family in Chadwick Street named }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 Stotts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 Stotts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 - they worked at Martindales }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 skin yard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 Skin yard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - what was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Er - taking the hides of the cattle when they'd been - er - when they'd killed them you know. And of course they used to leave on the ears - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well of course they could - they could
 take the fur - the fur off and all that and they could sell them you know for making blocks of soup. And I'd be round ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 The ears?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes. Oh yes, be up to - you could get anything in those days. It was the lips - they called 'em lips - it was th
e lips they used to keep at one side and the lugs and they called 'em lips and lugs - and I can remember many a time when we was - sure to meet them going down to this - er - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 skin yard}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - in - er - it's still there - getting three pen'orth of lips and lugs and mother used to now - er - clean them and - er - and - and make potato hash or - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh she'd take the fur off them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh she used to pull it all off but there might have been a few hairs left on 'em else when it was cooked you got it in your mouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you think that one lot of people thought themselves superior to the rest? Did you ever know of this happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Not in the working class area - but there was streets that if you - moved into they thought you were improving yourself and 
that was - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
'Cos they - they - er - well perhaps they were - they were perhaps a better class house. Now the people that moved - moved into what - and two streets no three streets - Bigland Street, Sunnyside Street and - er - Derwent St
reet - they were in Ordsall Lane district but - er - then they moved there of course they thought they were improving a little bit and - er - because they were a better type house and - er - I think much cleaner than where - not - much cleaner than where 
we lived, you know, and - I - I think they - them thought they were improving and - mark you if you was an engineer in those days and - you could have any girl because they knew you was on good pay - even though you worked for thirty bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you think of some families as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. Only the - the labourer knew they'd got more - less pay than the craftsmen, you know, because he
 was the chap who had the tools to get on with the job - but they never showed any distinction, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You don't remember any distinction?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well 
they were more or less all the one class then - down there - the workers you know, and - er - I don't think they - er - can't remember that - anybody they would be afraid of or anybody that - er - they couldn't face up to - then of course, they were very 
neighbourly as I've already said and - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your mother think of herself as being of a particular class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, no. She used to stand at the door }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6763823\charrsid7297954 somet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 imes - they used to sit at the door in the summertime, you know, all on stools. You'l
l have seen the stools well they sat on stools at the door and - er - they'd perhaps have a gill of beer in the jug - and put a drop in the glass and give Mary a drop then have a drop themselves. Yes, they were very neighbourly, you know, in the old days 
- they'd help one another and - er - I think they were a better class of people - from a neighbourly point of view than they are now, you know. I think so of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you think in those days you could move from one class to another - you could improve yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well - yes - it all depended on the kind of job you'd got, you see, and - er - well I started when I was left school as a nipper boy for the Great Northern Railway for five shillings a week. That was helping the van driver deliver the parcels you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember anyone that did move up in the world - when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - I can't remember. Children now when I see them as adults they - they're better clothed and better - er - and living under better conditions and surroundings, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady - and why do you think they were described like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Oh yes. Yes, well the police used to come down at ten o'clock at - er - at night - when they were changing over - they did the three shifts in those days - six til two - two to ten and ten til six - and - er - they come down in twos.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What did you think of the police in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well they were - they were a better type of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 policeman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - they wasn't educated - for it - er - but they were - they were a better class of man - for keeping law and order, you know
, because I'll tell you for why - if there was any fighting they didn't tell you twice to go you were out - were took up to Regent Road where they had - the cells - and charged with being drunk and disorderly on the Monday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you ever frightened by a policeman - did your mother ever say if you're naughty I'll tell a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - well of course she'd no need because they - we knew if we stood at the corner we got the cape round our neck and that was enough. The cape - the policeman gave us his cape and - told us to move on and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How do you think he treated the people though, the average policeman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well he - they used to try backs and fronts in those days you know - and I can remember quite clear ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Of every house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Of every house - I can remember quite clearly when the - er on the pub doors - back doors they used to leave a pint for the coppers and they knew - er - where to find it, you see, and - er - of course if they was chasing us we had - er - what they c
all middin doors and we used to open every middin door running up Ordsall so they couldn't get at us, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh this was a sort of square door in the wall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 That's right - it was yes. It came out - and I can also remember the time when the cle
ansing men used to work at nights only and - they - there was no toilets like we have today, you know, they were the open lavatories, you know, and they used to have to - you don't mind my telling you - they used to have to shovel it in a barrow - wheel i
t to the top of the end street tip it up and go back for more and then put it in the cart - load it up again in the cart - take it to Atholl Street - and they used to take it way on boats in those days to various farms along here, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And they had to actually empty the toilets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
They emptied the toilets and because - er - they were - er - it was an open lavatory, you see, no chains to pull or anything like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How do you think the police treated the people as a whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I
n those days? Well they kept among their own because they - they - er - they were afraid of them you see, because they - they knew they daren't say a thing wrong because - er - they'd be pulled in. And if they might saw the copper coming down the lane the
y'd say here's the copper and they'd be off before he had the chance, see. I remember some of the names - there was - er - Dominic Welby - do you remember Dominic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I've heard talk of him - very long arms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - and - er - er - and - er - he died 
in the Griffin in Chaff Street, you know - and - er - eighty years of age he was helping our lads in a rough and scramble in the tough and tumble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You remember him as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I do. I remember Dominic - I remember him getting the box - since - s
ince I been on the council - he hadn't finished his time then - telling the magistrates he chased this - er - fellow up a sin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6763823\charrsid7297954 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
cure - and they all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 old-timers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 they were, tell us what a sinecure is - well, your worship, it's one of them places that when you get in you can't get out - he meant a cul-de-sac.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 It was rented - we - rented and we paid seven and tuppence a week including the rates
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you ever see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh he came regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
He was very - very - oh he was a good one in those days - he was a man named Hall - and - er - I think he was a real good one. He did all the repairs and did not - not only did the repairs they allowed us to - er - beautified two r
ooms a year for seven and tuppence - and he would provide us with the paper and the labour. Mmm - oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well,
 we didn't take much interest in it those days because - er - how - where the money come - as long as the food was there - and so it was - it was there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You don't remember having any particular thoughts about it as you were starting to grow up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I never knew him to be ill and he was - when he was out of work he used to go looking for it and - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did he ever have to go to anyone for help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - we went once, I think, to the old Board of Guardians or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And - and I think he had to break stones in order to get - er - some relief. He had to break stones - you know the paving sto
nes - well he used to have to break them and flags that they brought in - break them into small portions for the purpose of making concrete, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 So your father went to them and they made him break stones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - yes - I think he got about sixpence an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did they feel about this - and how did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well - we didn't seem to bother - it seemed to be part of the system, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were they civil to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh yes - the children had more respect for the ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, I mean the Guardians, were they civil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Oh no - they were shocking - when I was on and that was long time after - that I went on in '35 - and I was made Deputy Chairman - well I was in - I was horrified at some of - the visitors'd come you k
now for relief and - it were on Eccles New Road then - do you remember the old work house - where the flats are now - workhouse was there and I was - er - on the committee there and I used to think this won't do me - er - have you got a piano in the house
 - yes - well sell it, and come back - all that lark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And did this happen in your father's day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes. In my day and in his day - you wasn't to have a decent home - if you had a decent home you couldn't get relief - or they - they'd make you get rid of something - sell it - and oh it was shocking, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 As a child who did you play with - did you play with your brothers and sister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I played with all the children in the street - and we played a - er - a lot of marbles but I remember on
e thing we used to do - Whit - er - Good Friday - we did all the pavements in - all - we - the pavement, not where the people walked, it were, you know, in the middle and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 In the edge of the pavement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. There was all - er - you've seen the pavement - the kerbing - not the - tar marked over them -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh I know what you mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well we used to chalk them with - er - from top end of street - this was part of our - er - chalking them with white chalk every cross - and - er - used to get a lot of enjoyment out of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you ever play in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1443249\charrsid7297954 
No we were more or less always outside because it was - er - if it were snowing we were delighted, you know, because we'd make snowballs and - we never was mischievous in my - I never hear of anybody going to Juvenile Court like for today you know.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What games did you play - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We played hop scotch - do you know what that is - hop scotch - we played that and then we - we used to turn a rope for the girls to jump i
n - you've seen the skipping ropes, you know, we used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well we always had a wash when we went to bed but er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did they get cross if you got dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes, you couldn't get - er - 
we wouldn't get dirty so much. Mark you, the - er - the cleansing of the city was more attended to than it is today - they - we used to have the old horse and carts coming down with - er - sweeping the pavements and side streets as well - you never see th
e
m now, you know. So there was no dirt - and everybody used to - er - to - er - er - do the outside of their flags - the front door - the flags - for so far under the window and the flags with - er - what they call - brown-stone. And inside mother used to 
do the hearth stone with - er - with - er - Blummell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
That's er - that's - er - kind of - er - instead of being a kind of a sand like they did for the outside it was a blue and when it dried it dried white - then we had the steel fender and the steel - er - kerb - er - fenders and ashpans, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What was a blumell made of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
It was made of the same stuff as sand - but it was a different colour, you see, yes, and the - they only used it for the hearth door you know, and I think they was two a penny. Two - one of each for two a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased or did your parents say there were certain children you hadn't to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - no objections - we all played together, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
There was no such thing in them - only one and we used to go - well it got that full we couldn't get in. That was in - er - the lad club at Ordsall Street - and the man that pioneered that and - er - was a 
man named Cliff and they made him a magistrate before he died for his services rendered.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 This was a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes. It's still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What sort of a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 It's - for the boys - you know for the boys - they had swinging and boxing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 But what did you do when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh we used to er - get on the swings, you know, and - er - swing. We used to think it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2370858\charrsid7297954 marvellous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  to Ordsall Park for a - for - er - for a Holiday - with a bottle of water, you know, you had no such thing as givi
ng 'em a shilling for a mineral. Bottle of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And how far was it to Ordsall Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well - it'd be as far as the - er - a - a couple - couple of - it's still there, Ordsall park, you know, but - er - then we had the swings as we could go on an
d - er - then Peel Park - we used to sometimes change and go to Peel Park - and there was a paddling pond there and we used - to enjoy ourselves in that, you know. Only with our shoes and stockings off, you know, of course we wanted a swim we used to go i
nto the River Bridge Water Canal over at - er - over the bridge at - er - quite coming to Hulme there, you know. With no trunks - we never bothered about trunks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did you spend your free time when you were at school - you just told me you used to go swimming - did you go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No, no. We usually played in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Then you kept pets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - hens - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Any other kind of pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - I - er - had a rabbit once - then when it became to friendly with a cat I got rid of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you collect anything or do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No. There was no gardens there in those days you know. Allotments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I know you went walks - you walked to the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Who did you go with when you went to the park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Oh it were two or three lads - we lot the girls join in as well - we - because - er - we all did things together and there was along we used to push 'em and they'd push us when we were on, you know and - er - we never ha
d much - there was no Juvenile delinquency in our day. We would never have thought - never have - wondered what it was all about if they come back and you talked about juvenile delinquency. Wasn't known. The parents used to keep them strictly now you know
 and home influence has got a lot to do with it, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - I tell you what - an amusing story - I used to go to Salford and carry the board round showing the change of players. I'd be about eleven and I used 
to get a tanner for that and I - I'd walk round the grounds - 'course there's no microphones in those days you know, I'd walk round the ground with this board and - er - and show all the spectators the change of team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you ever go to theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes - I - er - I used to go to the Regent - Mr Brown - well he used to have a bill in his window advertising the Regent and the artist, you see, and for that he got a free ticket and he used to take me and I've seen Sir Harry Lauder and Graci
e Fields and all these at the old Regent theatre - it - became the Palace after, you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about concerts and cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I - er - well yes. Once they used to show a - but there was no real cinemas then, you know, what they was was -
 er - pictures - the silent pictures, you know, and - er - we used to go to Wood Street and have a bowl of soup and very often there'd be a concert upstairs - and they had this silent film, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 This was while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 While I was still at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
They never had none to give us. Mark you, we used to go errands for the neighbours and then - like today - the children expect something for going - if we came back and they had a slice of bread and butter and jam that did us. And we got that very often }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1664636\charrsid7297954 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And you didn't mind if you didn't get a penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Relations or friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh one of the neighbours would pop in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh of cours
e, what happened is this - that there was no certified midwives, you know - there was what they called in the district - handy-woman - she could - she delivered all the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And your mother had this woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Aye, we had her as - her name was Mrs Robertson I think and we had one quite recently since we been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617120 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  who lived in Laudnum and we buried her about twelve month ago. And she was a hundred. Mrs Nichols. She was a handy woman as well - like - in my - we been }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617120 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  since 1917 and I can remember her quite well, 'cos there was no such thing ......
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Suppose a woman was very ill in those days, what happened, and the midwife couldn't bring the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well then they'd have to send for the doctor but - but very, very often - er - she
 - she was able to deliver the baby without any help. Where she got her experience from I cannot say - whether it was because she got it as - as - er - more experience as she went along delivering children but - there was no mishaps much - don't remember 
any anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What happened about the housework when your mother was in bed with the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well, we could always make an arrangement with one of the neighbours to pop in and keep her eye on things, see, and there's no, give her the idea of the day 
the baby was expected and - er - and - er - perhaps one of us or me father would go and knock at the door and say would you come in and explain that she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2370858\charrsid7297954 in labour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And they'd come in and help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - we - - er - we had no relatives living near - they didn't move out of Hulme - and I think many of them died in Hulme but - er - I've really forgot now whereabouts they did die.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh 
there was local friends - er - neighbours were friends, you see, and - er - but they never had any real - er - what shall I say - real friends coming to see us from over abroad or - as near as Blackpool and Southport but we had none there, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your mother and father have the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes - I think - er - when - er - the neighbours was mostly their friends. See they never went any father than the bottom of the street for a drink, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your mother have any special friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes, I think she had one down there - a woman named Melia Wayland - her first - she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617120 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  twice and her first husband was a man named Noble - she died perhaps twelve months or two years ago and she received a pension - a war pension 
from the first world war because her boy to her first husband was killed - his name was Willie. Then she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617120 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 again and - this - er - name was - er - the name Wayland - and when they left Ordsall Lane they moved them all to the same place - the flats on
 Eccles New Road and Melia was there as well as me mother, you know. Well they didn't separate them, you see - that were the first block of flats we built you know and we moved this Chadwick, Prescott Street, Garden Street, Fusia Street and Pump Street an
d Crookall Street we moved them all - well there's only odd shops down there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your father have any special friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - they'd get a drink of tea but there wasn't to give them to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Just on special occasions or did they come when they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - they just popped in said are you there and in they walked and - er - that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you think they were your mother's friends that were invited to your home or the friends of your mother and father both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well it was mother's friends you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your parents ever go to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, no. But me grandmother used to go and visit Little Webster sometimes because he always thoug
ht she had a bob or two. But I used to remember that when she - I - I always - smelt a rat when she was going because she got her bonnet out - she never wore her bonnet - only when she was going to see - they had little bonnets - with a thing under the ch
in, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
People say that in those days people made their own amusements - what do you think your parents did when they got together with friends or neighbours - did they play music or did they have games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well they sang and if anybody could 
play the public house - er - the piano in the public house it was - er - all right but if not they just - er - started and laughed and joked and - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Many people say that in those days society was divided into different social classes or groups in t
hat time before 1918 - did you think of some people belonging to one class and some belonging to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No - it was a strictly working class district - but if you got in some streets you was looked as better than - better than another - for instanc
e there was - er - er - Sunnyside Street and Bigland Street. The wages were a little higher they were engineers you see, if you got in those streets you were looked upon as - as having improved your conditions, you know. Then on Oldfield Road there was Pa
rsonage Street and Garden Wall Street - they were looked upon as the same but - er - they've deteriorated quite a lot and become slum property.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You don't remember any other things about the class system?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I was chiefly educated at St. Bartholomews Elementary School in Tartan Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How old were you when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I would be five - and - yes - and I left at thirteen. Yes 'cos they could leave in those days, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you go mornings and afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes. We went a full day to school in those days - starting a nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And what time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We got away at half past four - the school hours have not altered at all, you know, the children I don't think - the younger - the infan
ts went at four but the adults - those that had been transferred to the - er - those that - er - was getting a bit - wanted a little bit more education - have got this little bit more discipline - were transferred to the boys school and the girls schools 
upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 So it was separate boys and girls school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Oh yes - there - er - er - there was - when we were in the infants - that's what you want - ten years of age - they - they had boys and girls together - but then when they come to separat
e them the boys went to - er - to the boys department and the girls went upstairs to the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did you go to school and how long did it take?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Only took me five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you go on your own or did somebody take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh no, nobody ever took me - I could always ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Where did you have your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We came home to it when there was one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 But another day you went for pea soup, you told me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh yes. Well - er - it was - it was a place on Regent Road as used
 to - er - sell it - Mr Shepherd his name was - I've seen him about this last five or six years, he must be gone now though - and he used to - er - not - er - he used to let his hand slip sometimes and give us more than a penn'orth, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
I did - but there was a lot in it - too much discipline as I think it now - it's the best part - not too much discipline because I think you can give too much to children, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What did they discipline you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well, if they come behind you and found you'd got a figure wrong you got a thump in the back. You did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well, we always liked the headmaster - Mr Bullock - he - I can picture hi
m - you know, he wore a swallow-tail coat, you know, in those days - and then there was Mr Clayton - he had the end class-room - I can pic - and when I pass now I look at it - I think - well - he could tell if we'd moved when he come back 'cos the Tartan 
I
nn's at the corner and he used to pop out while the class - lessons were on - have a gill and nip back, you see. And we knew where he'd gone, you know. But - er - and then he come back and he could tell whether we'd moved. He was - he wasn't a certified t
e
acher either - it was loose - today I think they've got to be - in those days I think they were certified and uncertified wasn't it - and it affected their pay a bit if they was not - if they wasn't certified you know - but Clayton wasn't certified but he
 was a very good teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did they hit the girls as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well I couldn't tell you that because they were under a woman - Miss Rigby - upstairs - and the - never did - er - I don't think they were quite as keen but - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well we got - er - our - er - reports - er - I think it was once a year and mine was always fairly - I was good on some subjects and bad on others. I was good on scripture - I always got hundred per cent mark there 
but I was no good on figures much and I was good on geography and - er - and history I was good on - but - er - on figures I was - but I am now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We got the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - they never was invited to anything like they are today, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And were the children in the school all from the same type of home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Came - they came - yes - mostly from the same type of homes - er - perhaps with the exception of an odd one or two in a - and I can 
remember two boys as went there. They - they lived in Ordsall Lane until quite recently. At - er - a milliners shop - and they've gone within the last three months - the last - old tenants - father and mother had it before them - down this - must have bee
n seventy because they were the sons of the original proprietor you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did the teachers treat some children differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I don't think they did - I'll give 'em their due there - and - er - we used to know the odd ones that come
 from better class homes because they were differently dressed, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were there any gangs in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No they'd break that down - and there was no vandalism like there is today you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
No. No. I don't think - I think we all got - er - we were all together in the classroom and we all received the same amount of education - though some children was quicker at picking it up, we'll agree, than others, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And it was the same school - you just moved into another building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Would you have stayed on longer at school if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I think I would - although the education that I have - and I don't claim to have a lot n
ow - I think I've gathered it as I've gone along through life, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you go to any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - oh no. And I had a very large insurance book as you know and - er - I was never a penny out - I was most careful with me change, you
 know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You eventually became very good at figures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes. I could - er - now - I do a bit how weekend you know, and I do a bit for a coalman - Bill Roberts - he's very kind to me, he's got a pub and so he can't do the - he's got a pub in Ordsall Lane - the Albion - and mother used to .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you regret your education at all? Do you think you benefited from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Er - yes. Oh I was very good on the scriptures - I liked scripture lessons - and occasionally the Minister used to come from St 
Bartholomews Church and take the scripture lesson. I remember him very well, one - we had a man named Tom Shinwell, who became rector of All Souls, and he was there many years before he died - and he used to come and - you see - and I remember also when w
e
 paid tuppence a week school money. Well - er - of course - well - er - I suppose it was towards our education. There was - er - because - er - it was a church school and the education committee only allowed them so much you see, now they've done away wit
h church schools as you know, I think they're church schools in name only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have a part time job while you were at school? You told me you used to help a chap with greengrocery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Bill Brown - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well - er -
 he - he - that - I was just playing in the street and he - were - I used to like to go with him and he says will you come up to the stable with me and we used to go and look at the horse and - and somehow he got - me to brush it down and all that kind of
 thing. I've been in Shudehill Market at six o'clock in the morning with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What hours did you work when you were doing this part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well in summer time - on a - on a - it was chiefly Saturday and - er - Ordsall Lane used to be full of s
hoppers in those days you know and - er - well most - er - I used to - er - helped unload the cart when it come up to - up to the greengrocer - we always had to stop it between Shudehill Market to - er - the shop in Ordsall Lane and the stopping place was
 the Ellsmere Hotel and liked to - er - a drop of whisky and - er - and then - er - we'd start off again which is perhaps half a mile away and er - and the crowds of people that was - er - waiting for to be served, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you get paid for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well I - I - I - yes. I might have got a couple of shillings a Saturday night when I'd finished which was a lot - but I always got a couple of good meals, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well in those days - you - it was, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you give any of it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well no - I think I used to collect it, I'll tell you why. From then I started to save because I wanted a new suit and I used to put it under - you know the beds - like - it might be this chair at the bott
om - I used to put the money there but by gum she found it though. I used to think oh I got eighteen bob here but it was only sixteen when I come to look at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did the man treat you - who you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Very well. In the old days we used -
 er - the people used to come round from the various theatres to put bills in the shops advertising the shows for the following week - and as usual always gave - free passes, you see, and I used to go with him and we used to take - we used to go to the ol
d Regent theatre in Cross Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 So you used to like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I did - because we used to get the best of our - artists like Sir Harry Lauder, Vesta Tilly and all those, you know, and - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes I don't think I dislike
d it because we always provided me with two good meals - his wife was very keen - you couldn't go quick enough for her - but - er - he was very good - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did it alter your attitude to school when you were out at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You didn't have any other part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What about your first full time job - what was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Yes - me first full time job was five shilling a week and I went to the Great Northern Railway in Deansgate to be - er - an assistant to the 
driver and we loaded it with parcels and - er - and discharged them at the various places. We called em nipper boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well, I went down this - there seemed to be a lot starting along so I just went and asked and I got started, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What hours did you work for this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
It was eight o'clock in the morning you had to be there and I think you would finish about - be finished about - er - half past six at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you work Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. No. Saturday we'd work but not Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have a half day off then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well of course I was at school the remainder of the week yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No, when you did your full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh when I did me full - no there was no part time now. But I tell you what we u
sed to do - we used to have a fair on Ordsall Lane and that was our enjoyment - going down to the fair. And - er - er - they used to have a boxing booth there and there used to be a man come out with - er - boxing - er - gloves and ask who'd have a do wit
h one of their - two of their prize fighters, you know. Well we used to get a real good licking but we got the coppers after. I done that as well - and got a good - er - well - er - a good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13648271\charrsid7297954 
walloping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  - but they used to hold them in the crowd, you know, have them from the stage and they'd throw the boxing gloves have a do at their best - 'course they were trained, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you get holidays with pay at your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - we got a free pass at - er - at - er - just on - er - Easter - er - Maunda
y Thursday and we could go to - er - Southport for - er - with this free pass and - er - you see - er - I used to go to Southport - went about twice I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you think it was a fair wage that they paid you for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well perhaps it was in them days - but nobody'd look at it today - they want more than that in an hour don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you give any of this to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Oh yes. No - I gave her half of it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And what did she spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well - er - we used to be able to go to - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Did you get on with the people you worked with in this job where you were a nipper? After you were a nipper boy - what job did you go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I think I went to the Esso Petroleum there and I served with them for eleven and
 a half years. Finished in 1926. And I wouldn't go back because after the general strike they wanted to start us all as fresh starters and they didn't pay much wages - but they evidently - er - there was a pension at the end of it. There was no social sec
u
rity in those days and people worked really knowing - thinking that they'd be there til - for the future and being able to retire at pensionable age but it's the present day they should have looked after and seen they got a decent wage. Why - after the ge
n
eral strike was over I remember the leaders went to - er - to the - they had to give in - the leaders of that day - the government leader was MacDonald, Jimmy Thomas and I think that then - they was the people that was - er - let the workers down because 
t
hey - the workers were - wasn't ready to surrender - they were to - er - fight on for better wages because we were out in sympathy with 'em 'cos they was fighting for the miners. The miners like brought about the general strike - the T.U.C. advocated a ge
n
eral strike and we got one and I think that the men would have been prepared to - but the leaders of that day went and surrendered - and - er - when I first showed meself up again at the - er - the Esso Petroleum Company they wanted us to start as fresh s
t
arted and our - er - service in the past would - er - be counted as nought - but I wouldn't go back - I said that finishes me. But it was rather strange you know - a lot of men did go back because they had family, see, but I - I can remember now, when I w
a
s the Mayor I brought them all back from Maud Wheel - it was at Maudwheel - to Mayor's Parlor and give them a good dinner at night and we had a sing-song and I didn't know some of them - they'd changed that much - but - 'cos some had - masses of bushy hai
rs as lads and when they come to me - er - many years after - er - they - er - it had gone off and I had to say to the Manager, who was Mr. Davis - did you know Mr Davis - and Beale and then the yard foreman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 He was the manager, Mr Beale, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 H
e was in what they call the superintendent - the superintendent - and then they moved him because he was too friendly with - he thought a lot about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How did he treat you though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You liked him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I did - the trouble was this - you had to get hold of him sort of on the quiet if you wanted an advance. And we used to - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 How much an hour did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I was getting threepence halfpenny an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - we got holidays with pay - I'll give them that - yes we got a weeks holiday with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well we started at seven at one time and then we got it altered when got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13648271\charrsid7297954 
through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  to the union - from eight - to eight - eight til five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you work Saturdays there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 We worked Saturdays. And sometimes Sundays too to make up the pay - we got double time for Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And what was your job here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Well I was loading up lorries and - er - I - er - there's a man in our council now named Fred Brookes t
hat when he came in - some time - two years ago - three this next May - he recognised me and he said I used to load him up with the lorry and he was only twelve driving horselorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 When you left that, what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I took up an insurance book
 for the Salvation Army - and it - and it was payment by results so if there was no results there was no pay but - er - - er - they were keen tax disciplinarians but they'd pay - they paid you see, I could make a nice living even when I retired five years
 ago - I been retired just five years last month see - and - er - I thought I'd had enough but - er - I - er - I liked it - it helped me to help people when I got into their homes - it was in all kinds of difficulties.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Would you have chosen another type of job if you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I would have done - yes - because ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 You wouldn't have done insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
I would have done because - I saw right away - that it give me an opportunity to do something with the people - and I must tell you about how I was elected to the council
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you have to serve any apprenticeship or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No. The superintendent - no - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13648271\charrsid7297954 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  was - er - took me round one half day - he had two agents on his hands so he come to me one half day and he took 
the other fellow in the afternoon if he'd been with me in the morning - I think I was shown about - round about twice - and then that time I was left to paddle me own canoe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Were you a member of a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I was and still am - I'm an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13648271\charrsid7297954 honorary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
 member now - was a member - I've been a member of the Transport and General Workers Union - now I only pay a penny a week - that entitles me to - and I keep that up because I think it was - it's silly to drop it because no insurance would - er - would ta
ke me at me age - I get twenty-five pounds - er - twenty-five - er - death - I think - for a penny week - I think it's a good investment - and that's why I keep it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Yes - I was the branch secretary at one period and - er - and strange to say they were mostly corporation workers, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 And did you feel that the workers and the employers had the same interests or did you think their interests were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 I think they were - er - the 
employers those days wherever you went, disliked the trade unions - and - er - because - er - now - I was mover of the resolution in the council - to - er - conditions of employment should be - that was - that they should be members of the trade union - s
o that now before anybody starts - this - in every department - we sign a form to the fact that they're prepared to become members of a trade union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Did you feel that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13648271\charrsid7297954 there was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954  a division of interest amongst workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 No - I think they were very k
een knowing they were poorly paid and they saw that there was an advantage to - er - by being a member of a trade union - to get a fair crack of the whip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6453660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 Do you remember before 1918 what - was there a big difference between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14034234 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2916006\charrsid7297954 
Well - er - the - the - the trained people got more money, which was natural, you see, we got classified amongst the labouring class and - er - we had to - er, you know, we had to just - er - do as much work as we could. Mark you, there wa
s no room for slackers in those days - if anybody wasn't pulling their weight - five minutes to five when they found out there was a bit of slack period they'd - er - they'd - er - give you your cards at five minutes to five Friday night when you should h
ave been finished at five - nobody would know, they'd get their cards and - er - perhaps two or three days after they'd become busy the men'd be on the gate - they'd start from the back and that would mean they were fresh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
